<br>
A few other tips.<br>
<br>
1) If you have a lot of druids show up send several of the higher level extras in as a group to /assist Lady Vox and heal the one being eatten.<br>
<br>
2) If you have several 50+ tanks then tell the &lt;48 to not taunt as they will have enough of a problem just staying alive/unfeared.<br>
<br>
3) Bards mem that Desperate Durge spell so if all of your party gets killed and you're nearly dead let loose for a &quot;last great act of defiance ;o&quot;.<br>
<br>
4) If you have a low level &quot;little brother&quot; that tags along let them hold malechite/bones for Mage/Necro pet summons after they get toasted.<br>
<br>
5) To pin the dragon in the back of the lair do NOT attack it but run by to the back of the lair.  You will not get summoned until the dragon takes a certain amount of HP damage.  Until then you can lead it around.  ps. If your running the raid and also trying to pin the dragon back in the lair make hot keys with /shout Wave 2 attack! etc. or you may solo Naggy for 2 minutes before you remember...um.. no real basis in anything that's ..um.. ever occured before ;o. <p>Perciful Pellinore<BR>
Officer
